 :tx/rationale "ASSESSMENT PROPOSAL: Verification Sprint — 265 Untested INVs — Priority 2 (Sessions 48-52). PROBLEM: 265 current-stage invariants lack L2+ witness verification. This is the primary cause of F(S) stagnation — the specification denominator grows while the verification numerator stays flat. C6 (falsifiability) is at risk because falsification conditions exist in spec text but have no corresponding tests. SOLUTION: Freeze all new specification and feature work for 3-5 sessions. For each of the 265 untested INVs, add at least one L2+ witness test. Prioritize by F(S) component weight: V (validation, 0.18) and C (coverage, 0.18) first. Use the meta-test approach: for each INV-* in spec, verify at least one #[test] asserts its negation (falsification condition). FIRST-PRINCIPLES JUSTIFICATION: The convergence thesis (ADR-FOUNDATION-014) claims F(S) → 1.0 as the system learns. The saw-tooth model predicts dip (spec growth) then recovery (verification). We have 13 sessions of dip without recovery. The verification sprint is the empirical test of the convergence thesis itself. If F(S) rises to 0.72-0.78 after the sprint, the architecture is vindicated. If not, the thesis needs revision — and that is worth knowing before building more intelligence features. VERIFICATION APPROACH: (1) Measure F(S) before sprint (currently 0.62). (2) Track INVs verified per session. (3) Measure F(S) after sprint. (4) Target: F(S) ≥ 0.75, gaps < 50, untested INVs < 50. (5) If F(S) doesn't move, diagnose structural ceiling. DEPENDENCIES: Depends on Priority 1 (calibration fix) for accurate ΔF(S) measurements. Depends on Priority 3 (coverage bug fix) for honest baseline. UNBLOCKS: Saw-tooth model validation, F(S) movement proof, spec-impl gap reduction (142 → target < 50), ground truth for OBSERVER-4 calibration. TRACES TO: C6 (falsifiability), OBSERVER-4, ADR-FOUNDATION-014, ADR-FOUNDATION-020."
